print("TAREA 4 - Boxplot vista al mar:")
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
df.boxplot(column='price', by='waterfront', figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title('Comparación de Precios: Casas con y sin Vista al Mar')
plt.suptitle('')  # Quitar título automático
plt.xlabel('Vista al Mar (0: No, 1: Sí)')
plt.ylabel('Precio')
plt.show()

print("TAREA 5 - Relación sqft_above vs precio:")
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(df['sqft_above'], df['price'], alpha=0.5)

# Agregar línea de tendencia
z = np.polyfit(df['sqft_above'], df['price'], 1)
p = np.poly1d(z)
plt.plot(df['sqft_above'], p(df['sqft_above']), "r--", alpha=0.8)

plt.title('Relación entre Área sobre el suelo y Precio')
plt.xlabel('Pies cuadrados sobre el suelo')
plt.ylabel('Precio')
plt.show()

print("TAREA 8 - Pipeline con transformación polinómica:")
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, PolynomialFeatures
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline

# Crear pipeline
pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('poly', PolynomialFeatures(degree=2)),
    ('lr', LinearRegression())
])

# Ajustar pipeline
pipeline.fit(X_multiple, y)

# Calcular R²
r2_pipeline = pipeline.score(X_multiple, y)
print(f'R² con Pipeline: {r2_pipeline:.4f}')

cells.source:
print("TAREA 9 - Ridge Regression:")
from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score

# Dividir datos
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_multiple, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Crear y entrenar modelo Ridge
ridge = Ridge(alpha=0.1)
ridge.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predecir y calcular R²
y_pred_ridge = ridge.predict(X_test)
r2_ridge = r2_score(y_test, y_pred_ridge)
print(f'R² Ridge: {r2_ridge:.4f}')

print("TAREA 10 - Ridge con transformación polinómica:")

# Aplicar transformación polinómica a datos de entrenamiento y prueba
poly = PolynomialFeatures(degree=2)
X_train_poly = poly.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_poly = poly.transform(X_test)

# Crear y entrenar modelo Ridge con datos polinómicos
ridge_poly = Ridge(alpha=0.1)
ridge_poly.fit(X_train_poly, y_train)

# Predecir y calcular R²
y_pred_ridge_poly = ridge_poly.predict(X_test_poly)
r2_ridge_poly = r2_score(y_test, y_pred_ridge_poly)
print(f'R² Ridge con Polinomial: {r2_ridge_poly:.4f}')
